# Cursor Settings for Hously Project

## Frontend Package Manager
- Always use **Bun** for frontend operations (apps/web directory)
- Use `bun install`, `bun run build`, `bun run dev`, `bun run test`, etc.
- Never use npm, yarn, or pnpm for frontend dependencies

## Build Commands
- Always use Makefile commands for building:
  - `make build` - Build frontend for production
  - Never run build commands directly (e.g., don't run `bun run build` directly, use `make build`)

## Database Migrations
- Always use Makefile commands for database migrations:
  - `make migrate-new MESSAGE="description"` - Create a new migration
  - `make migrate-up` - Apply all pending migrations
  - `make migrate-down` - Rollback one migration
  - `make migrate-status` - Show migration status
  - `make migrate-history` - Show migration history
  - `make migrate-current` - Show current migration version
  - `make migrate-stamp REVISION="revision_id"` - Stamp database to a specific revision
- Never run alembic commands directly

## General Guidelines
- When suggesting commands or operations, prioritize Makefile targets when available
- Frontend development should always reference Bun as the package manager
- When creating scripts or documentation, use Makefile commands instead of direct tool invocations

